<div class=3D"para" id=3D"Chapter_02-direction-of-unit-vectors-2">The direc=
tion of a cross product is determined by the <dfn class=3D"terminology">rig=
ht-hand rule.</dfn> There are two ways to apply the right-hand rule, the th=
ree-finger method, and the point-and-curl method. You don=E2=80=99t need bo=
th, but you will need to master at least one to find the direction of cross=
