<div class=3D"para" id=3D"Chapter_02-direction-of-unit-vectors-3">The three=
-finger method uses the fact that your extended index finger, middle finger=
, and thumb are all roughly mutually perpendicular. If you align your index=
 finger with the first vector and your middle finger with the second, then =
your thumb will point in the direction of the cross product. Alternately, i=
f you align your thumb with the first vector and your index finger with the=
 second, your middle finger will point in the direction of the cross-produc=
t.<div class=3D"autopermalink" data-description=3D"Paragraph"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://engineeringstatics.org/cross-product-math.html#Chapter_02-direction-o=
f-unit-vectors-3" title=3D"Copy heading and permalink for Paragraph" aria-l=
